  "prompt": "Has anyone used IMCE Unzip in Drupal?",
  "response": "Yes, IMCE Unzip is an extension for the IMCE file management module in Drupal. It allows users to unzip files directly within the IMCE interface. This can be particularly useful for site administrators and content editors who need to upload and manage compressed files.\n\nTo use IMCE Unzip in Drupal:\n\n1. **Install IMCE Module**: First, you need to have the IMCE module installed and enabled on your Drupal site. You can find it on Drupal.org and install it using Composer or manually.\n\n2. **Install IMCE Unzip**: Download and install the IMCE Unzip extension. This can be done similarly using Composer or manually placing the module files in the `modules` directory.\n\n3. **Enable the Module**: Once installed, enable the IMCE Unzip module through the Drupal administration interface (`/admin/modules`) or using Drush.\n\n4. **Configure Permissions**: Make sure to configure the permissions for IMCE and IMCE Unzip so that the appropriate user roles can use the unzip functionality.\n\n5. **Use IMCE**: Navigate to the IMCE file management interface. When you upload a zip file, you should see an option to unzip it, allowing you to extract and manage the contents directly within Drupal.\n\nIMCE Unzip streamlines the process of handling zip files, making it easier to manage multiple files and assets within a Drupal site.",
